 to incorrect parameter estimates. However, the\ninclusion of X-ray light curves in different energy ranges can break this\ndegeneracy, and it therefore remains, in principle, possible to use X-ray data\nto derive fundamental parameters of magnetic cataclysmic variables, which\nrepresents an essential step toward understanding their formation and\nevolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Jul 2021 18:00:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-20"}
