umn setup revealed that chitosan is selective\nfor Ni over Ca and Cr with selectivity quotients of 9.6 (K Ni/Ca) and 3.0 (K\nNi/Cr). Overall, this study indicated that Ni complexation with SO42- enhances\nthe Ni adsorption capacity of chitosan, but slows down the adsorption process.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Jul 2021 22:22:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-26"}
